definition.value: N-Acetylneuraminic acid with alpha configuration at the anomeric centre.
The furanose form of D-tagatose.
A D-tagatofuranose with a beta-configuration at the anomeric center.
A D-tagatofuranose with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric center.
A D-tagatopyranose with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric center.
A D-tagatopyranose with a beta-configuration at the anomeric center.
An aldehyde in which a formyl group is located on a heteroarene.
A hydrochloride obtained by combining thiamine chloride with one molar equivalent of hydrochloric acid.
A hydroxyphenylalanine carrying hydroxy substituents at positions 3 and 4 of the benzene ring.
An organic compound that has a tetrahydronaphthacenedione ring structure attached by a glycosidic linkage to the amino sugar daunosamine and which exhibits antibiotic activity.
The D-glycero-diastereomer of alpha-D-manno-heptopyranose; a key structural component of the outer cell membrane in Gram-negative bacteria, found in the conserved core oligosaccharide region.
An alkane-alpha,omega-diamine that is dodecane substituted by amino groups at positions 1 and 12.
A nickel cation in which the nickel carries a triple positive charge.
An aluminium cation that has a charge of +3.
A cyclodextrin composed of seven alpha-(1->4) linked D-glucopyranose units.
A cycloamylose composed of eight alpha-(1->4) linked D-glucopyranose units.
An inorganic chloride of copper in which the metal is in the +2 oxidation state.
A semisynthetic penicillin antibiotic carrying a 3-(2-chlorophenyl)-5-methylisoxazole-4-carboxamido group at position 6.

A member of the class of indole-3-acetic acids that is indole-3-acetic acid in which the indole ring is substituted at positions 1, 2 and 5 by p-chlorobenzoyl, methyl, and methoxy groups, respectively. A non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug, it is used in the treatment of musculoskeletal and joint disorders including osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis, gout, bursitis and tendinitis.
An azo dye consisting of benzoic acid substituted at position 2 by a 4-[(dimethylamino)phenyl]diazenyl group.
A cysteine derivative that is the S-(2-aminoethyl) analogue of L-cysteine; reported to have cytotoxic effects.
A nickel cation in which the nickel carries a double positive charge.
